parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause a loss of essential vehicle information, including speed, fuel level, and warning lights, which can lead to accidents or other safety risks.
symptoms: The instrument cluster lights dim or go out
the speedometer and gauges do not function
the fuel level indicator does not work
the warning lights do not illuminate
and the entire instrument panel becomes dark.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the interior lighting can cause a loss of visibility and increase the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The dashboard lights dim or go out
the instrument cluster lights do not function
and the interior lights do not illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Airmatic suspension system can cause the vehicle to become unstable, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries to occupants and other road users.
symptoms: The vehicle's suspension system malfunctions
causing the vehicle to sag or drop
leading to uneven tire wear
damage to surrounding components
and potentially causing accidents. Warning lights may illuminate on the dashboard
indicating a problem with the Airmatic system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the high-pressure distribution hose can cause the Airmatic suspension system to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries to occupants and other road users.
symptoms: The vehicle's suspension system malfunctions
causing the vehicle to sag or drop
leading to uneven tire wear
damage to surrounding components
and potentially causing accidents. Corrosion of the hose may lead to oil leaks and further damage to the system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lower Control Arm Support Link Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the lower control arm support link can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and potentially lead to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle makes a creaking noise while turning the steering wheel
indicating a problem with the lower control arm support link.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster module can cause the lighting on the instrument panel to fail, making it difficult or impossible for the driver to read the gauges and meters, which can lead to accidents or safety risks.
symptoms: The instrument panel lights do not illuminate
the driver is unable to read the gauges and meters
the instrument panel is dimly lit
the instrument panel lights are flickering.
